        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 20:2-5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "To \"observe times\" was forbidden in the Law (marginal references), and was no doubt among the modes of divination practiced by the Canaanite nations. It has been explained as,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(1) Predicting from the state of the clouds and atmosphere;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(2) Fascination with the eye;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(3) Watching and catching at chance words as ominous.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Dealt with familiar spirits - This practice was forbidden by Moses Leviticus 19:31 under the penalty of death Leviticus 20:27. Its nature is best learned from Saul's visit to the witch of Endor (1 Samuel 28:7, etc.).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Dealt with familiar spirits - This practice was forbidden by Moses ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Leviticus 19:31",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " under the penalty of death ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Leviticus 20:27",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". Its nature is best learned from Saul's visit to the witch of Endor (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Samuel 28:7",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", etc.).",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Wizards - \"Wizards\" - literally, \"wise men\" - are always joined with those who have familiar spirits. Probably they were a sort of necromancers. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Wizards - \"Wizards\" - literally, \"wise men\" - are always joined with those who have familiar spirits. Probably they were a sort of necromancers. ",
            "children": []
